  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and slice your<strong> shallot[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>finely</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>tomatoes </strong>finely</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into small, bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1682436027610-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1682436027610-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1682436027610-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1682436027610-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1682436027610-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>shallot</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1682436032245-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1682436032245-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1682436032245-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1682436032245-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1682436032245-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomatoes</strong> and cook for 5 min or until beginning to break down</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1682436036144-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1682436036144-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1682436036144-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1682436036144-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1682436036144-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong> <strong>mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong> and 3/4 of your <strong>harissa paste</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml] </span><strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water </strong>– this is your <strong>harissa stock</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong> finely</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>cannellini</strong> <strong>beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1682436040332-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1682436040332-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1682436040332-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1682436040332-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1682436040332-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the tomatoes have completely softened, add the <strong>harissa stock</strong> to the pot with the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>potato</strong>, <strong>drained cannellini beans</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for 15-20 min or until the potatoes are fork-tender – this is your <strong>cannellini bean & harissa stew</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1682436044323-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1682436044323-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1682436044323-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1682436044323-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1682436044323-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the stew is cooking, combine your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>in a bowl with your <strong>ground sumac </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> – this is your <strong>sumac crumb</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1682436048896-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1682436048896-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1682436048896-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1682436048896-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1682436048896-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Spread the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>harissa paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) over each <strong>basa</strong> <strong>fillet</strong>, then top with the <strong>sumac crumb</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>basa</strong> <strong>fillets</strong> to a <strong>baking</strong> <strong>paper</strong>-lined baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until cooked through – this is your <strong>sumac-crusted basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1682436053081-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1682436053081-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1682436053081-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1682436053081-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1682436053081-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cannellini bean & harissa stew </strong>in bowls topped with the <strong>sumac-crusted basa</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
